# WHERE’S THAT POKÉMON?

## Complete Series Bible & Pitch Document

### Version 1.1 — Repo Reference Canon

-----

## THE LOGLINE

*Where’s Waldo?* meets the Pokémon universe — a large-format search-and-find book series, one book per region, 12–14 spreads per book, each spread a different iconic location rendered in a distinct art style. Each book includes exclusive promo cards printed in the back, featuring art pulled directly from that book’s spreads — collectibles you can’t get anywhere else.

-----

## THE CORE CONCEPT

**Format:** Large-format hardcover (approx. 12” x 9”), one book per Pokémon region.

**Structure per book:** 12–14 full-bleed illustrated spreads. Each spread = one iconic location within that region. Every location has its own distinct art style — the visual language shifts with every page turn to keep the experience fresh and prevent fatigue.

**The four engagement layers (every spread):**

|Layer   |What It Is                                                                                                                                                   |
|--------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|SEARCH  |Primary hidden Pokémon challenge. Difficulty tiered — common visible at a glance, mythicals hidden in reflections, shadows, background details               |
|DISCOVER|Mini-stories, hidden items, trainer cameos, evolution chains embedded in scenes for deep readers                                                             |
|COLLECT |Exclusive promo cards printed on card stock in the back of the book. Art pulled from that book’s spreads — location-specific, can’t be obtained anywhere else|
|REPLAY  |Layered find density means no two read-throughs surface identical details. Intentional replay value baked into structure                                     |

**Difficulty tiers (search layer only — not tied to collectibles):**

- Common — visible in main scene
- Rare — partially obscured
- Ultra Rare — hidden in background/reflection/shadow
- Legendary — one per spread, extreme difficulty
- Mythical — one per book, requires cross-spread clue chain

-----

## THE COLLECTIBLE MECHANIC

This is the differentiator no existing search-and-find book has executed — and it requires no app, no QR code, no redemption system.

**Perforated promo card pages are printed directly in the back of each book.** Card stock insert pages, 6–10 cards per volume. Each card features art pulled from that book’s spreads — the Gengar card looks like the Lavender Town spooky watercolor spread. The Lapras card looks like the Cerulean City watercolor spread. The art style of the location becomes the card’s visual identity.

These are cards you cannot get anywhere else. Not in booster packs, not at Pokémon Center. Exclusive to owning the book.

**Why this works:**

- No infrastructure. No app, no server, no redemption flow. Physical object in hand the moment you open the book.
- TPC precedent exists. They already produce promo cards for McDonald’s Happy Meals, Pokémon Center exclusives, and special events. A book-exclusive promo set is a natural extension of that program.
- The art style exclusivity is the hook for adult collectors. A watercolor Gengar card in a spooky illustration style doesn’t exist in the TCG. That’s a genuine collectible, not a reprint.
- Children understand it immediately. Find the Pokémon in the book. The card is right there. Done.

**Collector editions:** Foil treatment on cards, variant cover art, additional card per volume — natural SKU extensions for specialty retail (GameStop, Target card aisle, comic shops, Pokémon Center).

