## ART STYLE PHILOSOPHY

**Core rule:** Each location has one assigned art style. The style is not decorative — it is chosen to match the emotional register of the location.

The variety serves two functions:

1. Keeps the book visually fresh across 14 spreads — no two pages feel the same
1. Creates collectible card art that is location-specific — a Lapras card from Cerulean looks different from a Lapras card from Seafoam Islands

**Style range across the series:**

- Warm watercolor (pastoral, nostalgic)
- Classic anime line art (authentic to source)
- Pen & ink crosshatch (historical, dense)
- Bioluminescent watercolor (caves, night)
- Retro pixel / Game Boy palette (meta, playful)
- Pop Art / comic panels (urban, loud)
- Film noir high contrast (villain locations)
- Natural history illustration (wilderness)
- Dramatic TCG card style (climactic moments)
- Isometric cutaway (buildings, interiors)
- Art Deco travel poster (transport, movement)

**Publisher note:** All illustration executed by licensed artists working under The Pokémon Company’s art guidelines. Style direction and scene architecture provided by concept originator.

