## MARKET

**The Pokémon franchise** generates approximately $15 billion annually. It is the world’s highest-grossing media franchise. The TCG sells hundreds of millions of cards per year. The audience is multigenerational — children who play the games, parents who grew up with the original 151, adult collectors who buy TCG packs weekly.

**The search-and-find format** is proven and durable. Where’s Waldo? has sold 73 million+ copies across decades. The format requires no prior knowledge, scales from age 4 to adult, and has infinite replay value when layered correctly.

**The gap:** No existing product sits at the intersection of search-and-find + Pokémon IP + physical collectible unlock. This is the white space.

**Triple audience unlock:**

- Children (4+) — search and find is native format
- Families — shared activity, no screen required
- Collectors — rarity mechanic + physical cards drives adult purchase

